title: Trump fires up supporters in Florida
text:
Trump fires up supporters in Florida Jonathan Petramala, 11:29 p.m. EDT October 24, 2015 Trump fires up supporters in Florida (Photo: WTSP) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Wearing his trademarked red baseball cap, Donald Trump struck out at former Governor Jeb Bush at a Jacksonville rally. 
"Bush has no money, he's cutting, he's meeting today with mommy and daddy," Trump said to an estimated crowd of 14,000. "Here's a guy who wants to run our country and you can't even run a campaign." 
Trump spoke for an hour and a half in a speech that appeared to be totally ad-libbed. Donald Trump campaigning in opponent's turf 
10 news political expert Lars Hafner says Trump is fired up for a good reason. 
"I think he feels empowered since he's been leading in the polls in Florida," Hafner said. 
RELATED STORY: Trump: Bush can't run campaign, shouldn't run country 
According to the latest poll from the University of North Florida, of likely Republican primary voters out this week found Trump with the support of 22%. Ben Carson had 19%. Marco Rubio was third with 15% and Bush fourth with 9%. Read or Share this story: http://on.wtsp.com/1S3Cls6 TOP VIDEOS
